        {
            "type": "patchouli:spotlight",
            "item": "minecraft:beacon",
            "title": "The Beacon",
            "text": "A beacon is a block that provides players with various status effects in a radius around it."
        },
        {
            "type": "patchouli:text",
            "text": "To activate the beacon and gain its effects, you need to construct a pyramid-shaped structures underneath of it, built out of valuable resources, such as gold or iron.$(br)The beacon must not have any non-transparent blocks above it, in order to activate.",
            "title": "Activation"
        },
        {
            "type": "patchouli:text",
            "text": "Beacons can have serval tiers. The higher the tier, the more effects you gain access to.$(br)Constructing a larger beacon has the additional benefit of making your effects more powerful, through longer durations, and higher effect levels.",
            "title": "Beacon Tiers"
        },
